text: The loss of Reverend Billy Graham is a great sadness for our state, and for our country.  His legacy of servant leadership is an example to all of us.

Today, as I have multiple times in the last few weeks, voted to keep the government open. While I’m fed up with the broken budget process, it’s vital that we fully fund the Department of Defense and give our troops a raise they deserve – this bill does both.
